# Movie Recommendation System
This project is a **content-based movie recommendation system** built using Python, Pandas, and Scikit-learn.  
It recommends movies similar to a given movie based on textual features such as genres, keywords, and tags.
---
## Features
- Preprocessing of movie dataset (title, genre, language, overview, popularity, release date, vote stats).
- Text vectorization using **CountVectorizer** (bag-of-words model).
- Similarity calculation using **Cosine Similarity**.
- Recommendation function that suggests the **top 5 most similar movies** to any input movie.
---
## Tech Stack
- **Python 3**
- **Pandas** for data handling
- **Scikit-learn** (`CountVectorizer`, `cosine_similarity`)
- **Google Colab / Jupyter Notebook** for development
---
## Dataset
The dataset contains movie information such as:
- `title`
- `genre`
- `original_language`
- `overview`
- `popularity`
- `release_date`
- `vote_average`
- `vote_count`
You can find similar datasets on [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/utkarshx27/movies-dataset) or GitHub repositories hosting TMDb-based movie data.
